---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  path="/drum-lessons"
  title="Drum Lessons in McKinney, TX | Anthem Music"
  description="Drum and percussion lessons in downtown McKinney. Timing, technique, and groove for all ages - from first beats to full-kit control. Book a consultation.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow" style="justify-content:center;">Drums · Percussion</span>
      <h1 class="center">Drum lessons in McKinney</h1>
      <p class="lead mx-auto center">Timing, technique, and groove - from a student's first beats to full-kit control, taught the same way we teach everything: with the why included.</p>
      <div class="center" style="margin-top:1.8rem;"><a href="/schedule" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Consultation</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h2>Rhythm is the framework of all music</h2>
      <p>Every instrument at Anthem gets taught on top of rhythm - but for drummers, rhythm <em>is</em> the instrument. Our drum students learn the same musical framework as our guitarists and pianists: time signatures, note durations, patterns, and song form. The difference is they live inside it. A drummer who understands why a groove works - not just how to copy it - can sit down with any band, any song, any style, and hold it together.</p>
      <p>Lessons are built around each student. Young beginners start with the coordination and stick control their hands are ready for; teens and adults often come in wanting to play along with the music they love, and we build toward exactly that.</p>

      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature"><h3>Timing First</h3><p>Counting, subdivision, and metronome work that make every other skill possible.</p></div>
        <div class="feature"><h3>Technique</h3><p>Stick control, dynamics, and coordination - clean fundamentals before speed.</p></div>
        <div class="feature"><h3>Groove &amp; Feel</h3><p>Playing musically with real songs, not just exercises - locking in and serving the music.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2>What students build</h2>
      <p>Beginners work from pad and snare fundamentals into basic kit grooves - the rock and pop patterns behind most of the music they know. From there: fills, dynamics, reading rhythm notation, odd meters, and different styles. The consistent thread is playing <em>with</em> music early and often, because keeping time with a real song teaches what no isolated exercise can.</p>

      <h2>What a first lesson looks like</h2>
      <p>Every new student starts with a consultation - we get a feel for age, coordination, goals, and what music excites them, then build a plan from there. No kit at home yet? We'll tell you honestly what to start with and what to skip.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-band">
    <div class="container cta-inner">
      <div><h2>Start playing drums</h2><p>Book a consultation and we'll build a plan around your goals - and the music you actually want to play.</p></div>
      <a href="/schedule" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .page-hero { background: var(--cream-soft); padding: clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem) 0; }
  .page-hero h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .narrow { max-width: 760px; }
  .narrow h2 { margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .narrow h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .narrow p { color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .narrow p em { color: var(--navy); font-style: italic; }
  .feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr); gap: 1.5rem; margin: 2.5rem 0; }
  .feature { background: var(--cream-soft); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.6rem; }
  .feature h3 { color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 1.15rem; }
  .feature p { color: var(--gray); font-size: 0.95rem; margin: 0; }
  .cta-band { background: var(--orange); padding: clamp(2.5rem,5vw,4rem) 0; }
  .cta-inner { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 2rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .cta-band h2 { color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .cta-band p { color: var(--white); opacity: 0.92; max-width: 46ch; }
  .cta-band .btn-primary { background: var(--white); color: var(--orange-dark); }
  .cta-band .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--navy); color: var(--cream); }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { .feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>
